│[1m [0m[1mpatch_description       [0m[1m [0m│ Key ideas:                                                                                │
│[1m                          [0m│ - Replace the fixed-centers shrink approach with a two-stage optimization that tends to   │
│[1m                          [0m│ achieve a higher total sum of radii.                                                      │
│[1m                          [0m│ - Stage A: fix centers (carefully chosen in a hexagonal-like layout) and compute the      │
│[1m                          [0m│ maximal radii via a linear program (LP). This yields an exact optimum radii assignment    │
│[1m                          [0m│ for the fixed layout subject to wall and non-overlap constraints.                         │
│[1m                          [0m│ - Stage B: jointly improve centers using a lightweight simulated-annealing style          │
│[1m                          [0m│ hill-climb that repeatedly perturbs a randomly selected circle’s center and recomputes    │
│[1m                          [0m│ radii via the LP. Accept changes that increase the total radius, with stochastic          │
│[1m                          [0m│ acceptance to escape local optima.                                                        │
│[1m                          [0m│ - Use multiple restarts with different perturbations to improve robustness.               │
│[1m                          [0m│ - All circles remain inside [0,1]^2 and do not overlap; outputs stay the same format as   │
│[1m                          [0m│ the original program.                                                                     │
│[1m                          [0m│ - Deterministic seeds and modest iteration counts balance performance and runtime, while  │
│[1m                          [0m│ aiming for a sum of radii above the previous best (2.55) and closer to the known optimum  │
│[1m                          [0m│ (~2.63).                                                                                  │
