│[1m [0m[1mpatch_name              [0m[1m [0m│ enhanced_sa_seeded_packing                                                                │
│[1m [0m[1mpatch_description       [0m[1m [0m│ Introduce a more robust global search strategy: switch from a single multi-start local    │
│[1m                          [0m│ search to a diversified, seed-driven simulated annealing (SA) over centers, with          │
│[1m                          [0m│ LP-derived radii as the evaluation. This targets escaping local optima and exploring      │
│[1m                          [0m│ denser configurations (corner/edge placements often being critical). Key components:      │
│[1m                          [0m│ - A redesigned seed generator that builds dense hex/near-hex arrangements and fills gaps  │
│[1m                          [0m│ deterministically, then adds small jitter.                                                │
│[1m                          [0m│ - An inner SA routine that perturbs centers, re-evaluates radii via compute_optimal_radii │
│[1m                          [0m│ (LP), and accepts moves using a Metropolis-like criterion with a cooling schedule.        │
│[1m                          [0m│ - Multiple seeds to improve global coverage, plus an optional final refinement step using │
│[1m                          [0m│ LBFGS-B to polish the best found centers.                                                 │
│[1m                          [0m│ - Keeps the required interface and data shapes; higher sum of radii should improve the    │
│[1m                          [0m│ score and potentially beat the 2.635 target.                                              │
│[1m                          [0m│                                                                                           │
│[1m                          [0m│ This change is self-contained and leverages the existing LP-based radii computation, but  │
│[1m                          [0m│ uses a more principled stochastic/global search to push beyond previous bests.            │
